    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-732289">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-732289">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,732289)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-732289">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/bleggs" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(414493); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=414493&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227335" alt="bleggs" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=414493)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/bleggs" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(414493); return false;" >bleggs</a></span> <span class="odate time_1269362351 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Mar 2010 16:39</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-732289">
									

<p>It's not supposed to be an extant SCP. I'm assuming the in-universe Foundation has much larger holdings than our wiki.</p>
<p>On a side note, this is a perfect excuse for a rant. This is why I hate the -ARCs. If you're going to use a non-series SCP in your story, just write well enough that people can figure it out from the narrative alone. Or make them fill in the blanks themselves. You shouldn't have to write up supplementary material just so people can understand your story. They're never as good as regular SCPs, they get downvoted like crazy, and they never get deleted because they're an <em>essential</em> tie-in to someone's work.</p>

							</div>

								
					
